13-track CD album - Percolating with the nervous energy of Talking Heads, 
the stuttering punk-funk of Gang Of Four and the pulsating synths of The 
Cars, Jupiter One injects colourless indie rock with a bracing rhythmic pulse, 
two-fisted pop hooks and east coast swagger. The New York-based five 
piece produce an electrifying, invigorating sound that recalls the pogo-party 
frenzy of the late 70&#039;s / early 80&#039;s underground club scene, but with a 
contemporary guitar punch. Includes the single &#039;Platform Moon plus Bonus 
Recordings &#039;Umbrella&#039; & &#039;Summer Song&#039;
